## Visual Parity Check (Mandatory After Every UI Sprint)

After completing a sprint that ships UI, run this check before declaring the sprint done:

1. Open `docs/design-reference.html` in one browser window. Use browser DevTools to isolate the relevant section.
2. Open `http://localhost:5173` in another window. Navigate to the matching screen.
3. Put them side by side at 1280×720.
4. Compare: gradients, border colors, spacing, typography weights, shadow intensity, hover states.
5. If anything drifts beyond "minor spacing tolerance (±4px)", do NOT mark the sprint complete. Write a targeted Cursor prompt: *"Component X drifted from design-reference.html. Re-open that file, find selector `.X`, and port the CSS rules verbatim. Fix the divergence."*

This check is non-negotiable. Skipping it is how projects end up looking "kinda right but off" at the booth.
